article.headline: ETSU 90, Stetson 76
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Kevin Tiggs scored 37 points and Mike Smith notched a double-double to lead East Tennessee State in a 90-76 win over Stetson on Wednesday night in the first round of the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament. Smith scored 19 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for the Buccaneers (21-10), who finished second in the conference after winning three of their last four regular-season games. ETSU has won three straight overall. Courtney Pigram chipped in 15 points and five assists. A.J. Smith paced the Hatters (13-17) with 24 points and Tim Lang also recorded a double-double, scoring 18 points and pulling down 12 boards. He also tallied four blocks. Mark Lohuis added 11 points and Garfield Blair had 10 for Stetson, which ended its season on a five-game losing skid. The Buccaneers led by four at the break, but outscored the Hatters 53-43 in the second.
